messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

```json
[
  {
    "path": "/*",
    "handler": "DefaultController.handleOptions",
    "implementationPresent": true,
    "pathIsPrefix": false,
    "pathIsLiteral": true,
    "pathIsConvention": false,
    "isRestApi": true,
    "isTestApi": false
  },
  {
    "path": "/",
    "handler": "DefaultController.index",
    "implementationPresent": true,
    "pathIsPrefix": false,
    "pathIsLiteral": true,
    "pathIsConvention": false,
    "isRestApi": true,
    "isTestApi": false
  },
  {
    "path": "/api/secured",
    "handler": "DefaultController.secured",
    "implementationPresent": true,
    "pathIsPrefix": false,
    "pathIsLiteral": true,
    "pathIsConvention": false,
    "isRestApi": true,
    "isTestApi": false
  },
  {
    "path": "/login",
    "handler": "DefaultController.login",
    "implementationPresent": true,
    "pathIsPrefix": false,
    "pathIsLiteral": true,
    "pathIsConvention": false,
    "isRestApi": true,
    "isTestApi": false
  }
]
```

**Explanation:**

The code provided contains four API entries, each defined using the `@RequestMapping` annotation.

1.  **`/*`**: This entry handles `OPTIONS` requests to any path. The path is a literal string. The handler is the `handleOptions` method of the `DefaultController` class. The implementation is present in the same file. It is a REST API entry.
2.  **`/`**: This entry handles `GET` requests to the root path. The path is a literal string. The handler is the `index` method of the `DefaultController` class. The implementation is present in the same file. It is a REST API entry.
3.  **`/api/secured`**: This entry handles `GET` requests to the `/api/secured` path. The path is a literal string. The handler is the `secured` method of the `DefaultController` class. The implementation is present in the same file. It is a REST API entry.
4.  **`/login`**: This entry handles `POST` requests to the `/login` path. The path is a literal string. The handler is the `login` method of the `DefaultController` class. The implementation is present in the same file. It is a REST API entry.

All paths are extracted from literal strings in the `@RequestMapping` annotations. None of the entries are for testing purposes.

path.description: The HTTP request path, which must begin with a forward slash (/) and have path parameters wrapped in curly braces ({}). Set this to null if it cannot be determined.
path.title: Path

handler.description: The function, class, class method, or object that handles the HTTP request. Use exactly "anonymous" to denote an anonymous implementation.
handler.title: Handler

handler_in_same_file.description: Whether the handler's implementation is present in the same source code file, rather than being imported.
handler_in_same_file.title: Handler In Same File

path_is_prefix.description: Whether the path string is a prefix rather than a full path.
path_is_prefix.title: Path Is Prefix

path_from_string_literal.description: Whether the path string is extracted from a literal string defined in the source code.
path_from_string_literal.title: Path From String Literal

path_from_naming_convention.description: Whether the path string is derived from a naming convention supported by the framework.
path_from_naming_convention.title: Path From Naming Convention

is_restful_api.description: Whether the API entry is for a RESTful API, rather than other types of APIs.
is_restful_api.title: Is Restful Api

is_testing_purposes.description: Whether the API entry is intended for testing purposes, such as unit tests or functional tests.
is_testing_purposes.title: Is Testing Purposes
